        <h3><strong>Real-Time Event Tracking</strong></h3>
        <p>
          Building on this ownership model, Fan Game Cube tracks game events in real-time, automatically crediting points to NFT holders when action occurs at their field locations. The system processes live game data to ensure accurate, immediate reward distribution.
        </p>
        <p>
          This real-time engagement keeps fans actively involved throughout matches, not just during obvious scoring moments. Every play becomes meaningful to fans who own the zones where action unfolds, creating sustained attention across the entire game duration.
        </p>
        <p>
          As a result, the point system creates competitive dynamics among fans, with leaderboards and achievement tracking that encourage ongoing participation. This gamification extends engagement across multiple games and seasons, building long-term fan investment.
        </p>
        <h3><strong>New Revenue Streams for Clubs</strong></h3>
        <p>
          Sports clubs leave significant revenue on the table when fan engagement ends after the final whistle. Fan Game Cube monetizes this ongoing fan interest through NFT sales and secondary market activity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Clubs can issue limited edition field zone NFTs for marquee matches, create season-long ownership programs, or offer special zones tied to star players. Each NFT sale generates direct revenue while simultaneously building deeper fan relationships and loyalty.
        </p>
