            <li>Secondary market activity generates ongoing engagement and potential royalties</li>
            <li>Leaderboard systems drive competitive participation across fan bases</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <h3><strong>Global Sports Implementation</strong></h3>
        <p>
          The platform is built for global sports implementation, adapting to different playing fields, rules, and fan cultures. Football clubs can divide the pitch into NFT zones, while chess implementations map board squares to digital ownership.
        </p>
        <p>
          Similarly, tennis implementations focus on court zones where serves and winning shots occur. Cricket adaptations track field positions relevant to boundaries, catches, and run-scoring areas, ensuring sport-specific relevance.
        </p>
        <p>
